<body class="antialiased">

<!-- Chosen Palette: Warm Neutrals with Blue (Case 1) and Orange (Case 2) accents. Background #f8fafc (Slate 50), Text #334155 (Slate 700). Case 1: #0ea5e9 (Sky 500). Case 2: #f59e0b (Amber 500). -->
<!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page dashboard format was chosen to allow users to linearly or non-linearly explore the engineering trade-offs. It features a sticky navigation bar for quick jumps. Section 1 introduces the core physical problem (flow variation). Section 2 provides interactive tabs to compare the architectural logic of the two solutions. Section 3 presents quantitative visualizations of the engineering assessment (Radar for qualitative scores, Bar for scale multipliers). Section 4 delivers the final conclusion. This structure transforms a dry engineering report into an interactive consulting presentation. -->
<!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. Flow Profile -> Line Chart (Goal: Change/Compare over time) -> Shows A Tank peak vs Case 1 flatline vs Case 2 mimic. 2. Scenario Architectures -> Tabbed Text (Goal: Organize) -> Allows easy toggling without cluttering the screen. 3. Multi-dimensional Eval -> Radar Chart (Goal: Compare) -> Visually demonstrates the trade-offs (CAPEX vs OPEX vs Stability). 4. Scale Quantified -> Bar Chart (Goal: Compare magnitude) -> Highlights the 7.05x scale difference powerfully. All use Chart.js on Canvas. NO SVG used. -->
<!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->

